&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Purchase to Pay Assistant - 37.5 hours per week&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen within the CHoICE Procurement Services – Purchase to Pay [P2P] Team for a P2P Assistant.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will be based at South Tyneside Hospital. Travel may be required for off-site meetings.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The purpose of the role is to provide and efficient, secure, safe accurate and timely service for the receipt and payment of invoices&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need to be able to work under your own initiative without close supervision, be literate and numerate with excellent customer service and organisational skills. Good and clear verbal communication and interpersonal skills are vital to this role as you will be liaising with various members of hospital staff working across all levels.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates should have administration experience and be highly motivated to providing a first class Procurement Service to ensure that clinical services can be delivered effectively.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer a supportive learning environment and encourage staff to build their skills through work-related courses and internet based learning.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Contact details for job related candidate queries:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Mr I Graham&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Deputy Procurement Operational Manager&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Tel: 0191 5656256 Ext 41433&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
